&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Staff Nurse Band 5 Children&#39;s Community Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;SECONDMENT OPPORTUNITY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;37.5hrs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed Term 6-9 months -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To contribute to the provision of high standard of nursing care for neonates, children, and young people with life limiting/life threatening conditions people and their families within the community of Torbay affiliated to South Devon Healthcare Foundation Trust. The job will encompass working across acute areas involving a generic community approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To enable the child or young person and their family to lead as free as possible life from clinical and psychological complications, and to promote good practice in the assessment, diagnosis, treatment and care of children and young people.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;He/she will assist in the assessment of care needs and the development, implementation and evaluation of appropriate programmes of care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post will encompass flexible working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
